If Fridge, Martha, and the 2 granddads are in the game, then that leaves out the possibility that Bethany didn't go in the game. Note that we didn't see the game suck Bethany in. text: The original movie was so intriguing because it had a calm mystery vibe to it in the beginning.  Then when it captured your attention, the leading actors find the board game which further enhances your curiosity.  Finally the leading actors begin the game which ultimately led to consequences and the suspense in the movie.   There was some comedy placed in certain parts which changed things up, but overall it kept that intensity until the game was finished.    This on the other hand has some well known actors for sure, but the whole serious mystery vibe you can tell is already replaced by sarcasm and silliness.  I'm not saying it will be a bad movie, but at the same time I can't understand what it is with Hollywood 2019 and trying to make every dam sequel a comedy show.

text: @ Sony Pictures - @ Columbia Pictures: I'm really very happy that "JUMANJI" gets a new coinematographic sequel but I also hope that, in the future, Columbia Pictures will also decide to make a prequel movie; The first film, produced in 1995, began with a scene set in the year 1869, where two boys, Caleb and Benjamin, bury, frightened, a mysterious underground box, which only later we  understand contains the game Jumanji; I would very much like a prequel to be made, which treats just that game challenge , made in 1869; The film, if ever you decide to make it, should end with that scene, shown as an incipit in the 1995 film! Obviously, in the prequel there should be new players, even if to bury the mysterious box will be Caleb and Benjamin, who will not be present in the film, since the actors are now grown! The prequel would have a lot of charm because: set in the hear  past, Jumanji is still a board game and not a video game and maybe, using the narrative style of the original movie "1995" decidedly more beautiful than the sequel of "2017", although I appreciated very much that movie too!
